---
import StarlightPage from '@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro';
import Hero from '../components/home/Hero.astro';
import { YouTube } from 'astro-embed';
import { Code } from '@astrojs/starlight/components';

const code = `MapView(
    onMapClick = {
      // onMapClickAction
    }
) {
    for (markerState in markerList) {
        Marker(state = markerState)
    }
}`;

const content = {
  title: 'MapConductor',
  description: 'Write map code once. Run it on any map SDK.',
  subtitle: 'One API for every map SDK',
  heroMessage: `Stop rewriting\nmap code.`,
  buttons: {
    getStarted: 'Get Started',
    developers: 'View Docs'
  }
};
---

<StarlightPage frontmatter={{ title: content.title, description: content.description }}>

  <Hero
    title={content.title}
    subtitle={content.subtitle}
    heroMessage={content.heroMessage}
  />

  <!-- VALUE PROPOSITION -->
  <div class="sl-markdown-content home-summary">

  <p><strong>Write once. Run on any map SDK.</strong></p>

  <p>
  MapConductor is an open-source unified map SDK for mobile developers.
  Use Google Maps, Mapbox, HERE, ArcGIS and more — all through one consistent API.
  Focus on building your map experience, not rewriting integration code.
  </p>

  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div style="display:flex; gap:1rem; margin-top:2rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <a class="sl-link-button"
       href="/intro"
       style="padding:0.75rem 1.5rem; background:var(--sl-color-accent); color:white; border-radius:0.5rem; font-weight:600;">
      {content.buttons.getStarted}
    </a>

    <a class="sl-link-button"
       href="https://docs-android.mapconductor.com/"
       style="padding:0.75rem 1.5rem; background:transparent; color:var(--sl-color-accent); border:2px solid var(--sl-color-accent); border-radius:0.5rem; font-weight:600;">
      {content.buttons.developers}
    </a>
  </div>


  <!-- QUICK BENEFITS -->
  <div class="sl-markdown-content home-summary">
    <h2>Why MapConductor?</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>One API, multiple map providers</strong> — no SDK rewrites</li>
      <li><strong>Switch providers anytime</strong> without vendor lock-in</li>
      <li><strong>Built for modern mobile UI</strong> (Jetpack Compose & SwiftUI)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>


  <!-- CODE FIRST (ENGINEERS SCAN THIS) -->
  <div class="sl-markdown-content home-summary">
    <h2>Simple Unified API</h2>

    <Code code={code} lang="kotlin" />

  <p> The same code works across supported map SDKs. Think of it as <strong>jQuery for map SDKs</strong>. </p>
  </div>
  <!-- VIDEO -->
  <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <YouTube id="https://youtu.be/Sh2GAsM7Qe8" title="MapConductor Introduction" />

  <!-- FEATURES -->
  <div class="sl-markdown-content home-summary">
    <h2>Key Capabilities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Multi-SDK Support</strong><br/>
      Operate Google Maps, Mapbox, HERE, ArcGIS and more from a single codebase.</li>
    
      <li><strong>Unified Map API</strong><br/>
      Display markers, shapes, camera controls, and events consistently.</li>
    
      <li><strong>Freedom from Vendor Lock-in</strong><br/>
      Change map providers without rewriting your application logic.</li>
    
      <li><strong>High-Performance Rendering</strong><br/>
      Built-in algorithms handle thousands of markers smoothly.</li>
    
      <li><strong>Modern UI Support</strong><br/>
      Designed for Jetpack Compose and SwiftUI workflows.</li>
    </ul>
  </div> <!-- DEMO -->

  <YouTube id="https://youtu.be/uGjpXKX0a4w" title="Android Demonstration" />

  <h3>Featured</h3>
  <a href="https://orynth.dev/projects/mapconductor" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img src="https://orynth.dev/api/badge/mapconductor?theme=light&style=default" alt="Featured on Orynth" width="260" height="80" /></a>
</StarlightPage>
